        "cooked": "<p>When you highlight a piece of text in a message draft and apply formatting (e.g. italic or bold), the menu for formatting immediately closes and the text loses its highlight. This is a bit inconvenient if youâ€™re applying multiple formatting options; I feel it would be better if the highlight had to be <em>explicitly</em> removed (by tapping elsewhere in the text, similar to what happens after you copy a selected portion of text), and even the same for the formatting option. That is, to have the format menu close only after the user explicitly gestures for it to do so.</p>",
